  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. The model predicts absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device operating at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors; seven factors were formally assessed and six were scoped out due to epistemic limitations at MRL 5. All assessed factors achieved required levels under the Minimal profile evaluation criteria. Intended use scope, device class, and operating envelope are described in the Claim and Requirement nodes bound below; the structured Context of Use object is not separately linked under this profile registration.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cfd-hemolysis-absolute-vad",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-experimental-2019",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-hemolysis-monte-carlo-outputs-2024"
  ],
