    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou2-minimal-dr-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-cva-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Under the Minimal profile evaluation criteria, the seven assessed credibility factors collectively demonstrate sufficient model credibility for the intended use of CFD-predicted hemolysis in the VAD regulatory submission. The six not-assessed factors are acknowledged as epistemic gaps but are accepted under the Minimal profile's reduced documentation threshold. The decision team notes that the Claim and Requirement nodes bound to this UoA contain detailed prose specification of the intended-use scope, device class (Class III), operating envelope (2000–3500 RPM, 3–7 L/min), and patient population. Accepted with the condition that not-assessed factors be resolved prior to any elevation to a Complete profile assessment.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
